# 2️⃣ Inheritance (🔥 MOST IMPORTANT OOP TOPIC)

This is one of the MOST ASKED placement questions.

---

# First Understand the Problem

Suppose:

```text id="jlwmle"
Car
Bike
Truck
```

All have:

* speed
* start()
* stop()

Why rewrite same code again and again?

---

# Solution → Inheritance

---

# Simple Idea

👉 One class can reuse properties/functions of another class.

---

# Real-World Example

Child inherits:

* surname
* properties
* features

from parents.

Same idea in programming.

---

# Example

```cpp id="jlwm0m"
class Vehicle
{
public:

    void start()
    {
        cout << "Vehicle Started";
    }
};

class Car : public Vehicle
{
};
```

---

# What Happens?

`Car` automatically gets:

```text id="8jlwmn"
start()
```

from `Vehicle`.

---

# Usage

```cpp id="jlwmu9"
Car c;
c.start();
```

---

# Why Inheritance Exists

To:

* avoid duplicate code
* improve reusability
* create hierarchy

---

# Mental Model (VERY IMPORTANT)

```text id="9jlwmq"
Parent class → common features
Child class → specialized version
```

---

# Terminology

| Term          | Meaning |
| ------------- | ------- |
| Base Class    | Parent  |
| Derived Class | Child   |

---

# Visualization

```text id="jlwm9f"
Vehicle
   ↓
Car
```

---

# Types of Inheritance

---

## 1. Single Inheritance

```text id="8jlwmx"
A → B
```

---

## 2. Multilevel Inheritance

```text id="jlwm5v"
A → B → C
```

Like:

```text id="qjlwmz"
Grandparent → Parent → Child
```

---

## 3. Multiple Inheritance

```text id="jlwm0x"
A + B → C
```

Child inherits from multiple parents.

---

# Why Interviewers Love Inheritance

Because it tests:

* OOP understanding
* hierarchy thinking
* software design

---

# Common Mistake 🔥

Private members are NOT directly accessible in derived class.

---

# Example

```cpp id="7jlwmh"
class A
{
private:
    int x;
};
```

Derived class cannot directly use `x`.

---

# How to Remember Forever

```text id="2jlwmr"
Inheritance = reuse existing code
```

OR

```text id="rjlwmw"
Child gets features from parent
```

